    </mj-text>
    <mj-text color="#212b35" font-size="12px" height=15px font-weight="bold">
      Margo Donohue ’22, Sports Editor

    </mj-text>
    <mj-text color="#637381" font-size="16px">
      After the Garland residents finish spending the two-week quarantine playing golf on the seventh fairway, they could find themselves on the athletic field, exploring the school’s trails, or participating in the Math Team.<br>This school year has arrived with many changes, and the fall co-curricular program is no exception. Students can now choose from 36 interscholastic teams, intramural activities, outdoor programs, and alternative team options in the fall, more opportunities available than ever before.

